import React from 'react';
import { BrowserRouter as Router, Route, Switch } from 'react-router-dom'
import Layout from './components/Layout'
import NavigationBar from './components/NavigationBar'
import Jumbotron from './components/Jumbotron'
import HomePage from './components/pages/HomePage'
import ProjectsPage from './components/pages/ProjectsPage'
import NoMatchPage from './components/pages/NoMatchPage'
import ExperiencesPage from './components/pages/ExperiencesPage'

// We use React.Fragment to have multiple page components side by side (NavigationBar, Jumbotron, Router Layout)
function App() {

  return (
    <React.Fragment>
      <Jumbotron title={"ALLISON WU"} />
      <NavigationBar />
      <Layout>
        <Router>
          <Switch>
            <Route exact path="/" component={HomePage} />
            <Route exact path="/projects" component={ProjectsPage} />
            <Route exact path="/experiences" component={ExperiencesPage} />
            <Route component={NoMatchPage} />
          </Switch>
        </Router>
      </Layout>
    </React.Fragment>
  );
}

export default App;
